window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><b>From USA Today bestselling author Dakota Davies comes an all new small town suspense romance about a broken military hero and the soft-hearted girl he’ll burn the world down to save.</b></p> <p>She’s my best friend, the one that got away, and now, my nemesis.</p> <p>Six years ago, I spent the night with my best friend. Maybe it was the pretty wedding we'd attended together and the champagne, or maybe it was how she looked at me that night, like I mattered.</p> <p>Or maybe it’s that I’ve been in love with Ava Greely for longer than I care to admit.</p> <p>When she ran the next morning, begging me to forget the best night of my life, I did what I always do, stuffed my broken heart back where it belongs and returned to duty.</p> <p>Six years later, a family emergency calls me back to Finn River, and directly into Ava’s path. We try to avoid each other, but the sparks between us have only intensified with time, and in one powerful moment, they catch fire.</p> <p>But Finn River is hiding secrets that threaten to tear us apart. Someone’s been watching us, and they don’t like what they see.</p> <p>When the threat closes in on Ava, can I piece the clues together in time to save her?</p> <p>And when the military beckons, how will I choose between my duty and a chance at love?</p> <p><i>Author's note: A military hero secretly falling for the pediatrician making her small town a better place one fix at a time. Add in a boisterous found family, plenty of mountain town shenanigans, forbidden heat, suspense, and a heartwarming HEA.</i></p> <p>Love Me Fearless is a standalone small town contemporary romance novel and book three in the unforgettable Love Me Dangerous series.</p>"; 
